How to PCVR
1-Unpack the ISO or ZIP and follow any instructions to install.  Some games do not require installation.
2-Link the game to Steam.  Bottom-left corner of Steam, Add a Game > Add a non-steam Game > Browse > Select the .exe file of the game in question
3-In your Steam Library, right-click > Properties, and check "Include in VR Library"

To launch the games, open SteamVR from either Virtual Desktop or Oculus Link, and click "All Games" if it doesn't appear on the short list.  Your games will be under "Local".

PCVR Troubleshooting
-Edit launch command, adding the -steam to the end.  For example, "whatever.exe" -steam
-Try adding -HmDEnable 1

Most patched games do not have multiplayer working.  Dead & Buried 2, Drunkn Bar Fight, Elven Assassin, and Onward are reported to work, however.

Can I get banned or brick my device?
There have been no reports of anyone getting banned from pirating or sideloading.

It is very unlikely that you will brick your device if you use sidequest or AndroidSideloader and you follow all the instructions and don't mess with files you're not sure about.

Next, open the ADB-TCPIP folder and double-click the "Enable ADB-TCPIP" batch file. Leave this CMD window open and your Quest plugged in. 

Put on your headset and navigate to the "Channels" tab (All Apps > TV > Channels) and the new tweaks can be found here. They can also be found in "Unknown Sources". Click on one of the tweaks and your screen will go black for a second, it will then ask you to allow USB Debugging. Click allow and it will take you back to the "Channels" tab. You must then click on the same tweak again, your screen will fade to black (this is how you know it's working) but this time it will apply the tweak. Do this for each tweak you want to apply. 

You will need to enable USB Debugging for each of the specific tweaks you want to use but will only need to do this once. The next time you apply a tweak you've granted permissions for, the screen will just fade to black. 

Also, every time you restart your Quest, you will have to apply the tweaks again, meaning you need to run ADB-TCPIP again (using batch file) and have your Quest hooked up to your PC.

Recommended Settings:
Disable Throttle, 1536x (Or 2048x for Lower-End Games), Fixed Foveated Rendering High (or High-Top), GPU-CPU Level 4.
